About this hotel

A 3-minute walk from Torre Glòries tower, this sleek hotel is 5 km from the Plaça de Catalunya, a central square, and 6 km from lively La Boqueria market.

Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    El Parc i la Llacuna del Poblenou

    Developing area El Parc i la Llacuna del Poblenou is defined by ultramodern corporate and cultural architecture, including the iconic geyser-shaped Glòries Tower and adjoining Barcelona Design Museum. Can Framis Museum shows contemporary Catalan painting in a renovated 18th-century factory. The surrounding streets are lined with mainstream boutiques, tapas bars and casual pubs,.

    About this hotel

    A 3-minute walk from Torre Glòries tower, this sleek hotel is 5 km from the Plaça de Catalunya, a central square, and 6 km from lively La Boqueria market.…

    Chic rooms offer free Wi-Fi and flat-screens, plus minibars, and tea and coffeemakers. Some include colorful murals, Mediterranean tiles, terraces, pull-down beds and/or whirlpool tubs. Upgraded rooms have porch swings and dining areas. Room service is available.

    There’s a Mediterranean restaurant/bar; a breakfast buffet is offered for a fee. Other amenities include a gym, a sauna and a hammam, plus a rooftop terrace with an outdoor pool and a bar. Bike rentals and parking are available.
